# Testing & Quality Assurance

## Testing Strategy

### Test Categories
- **Unit Tests**: Test individual functions and classes
- **Integration Tests**: Test component interactions
- **End-to-End Tests**: Test complete user workflows
- **Performance Tests**: Test system performance under load
- **Security Tests**: Test security vulnerabilities
- **Accessibility Tests**: Test UI accessibility

### Test Organization
```
tests/
├── unit/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── services/
│   ├── utils/
│   └── fixtures/
├── integration/
│   ├── api/
│   ├── database/
│   └── external/
├── e2e/
│   ├── scenarios/
│   └── journeys/
└── performance/
    ├── load/
    └── stress/
```

### Test Quality Standards
- Tests should be readable and maintainable
- Use descriptive test names (Given-When-Then format)
- Implement proper test isolation
- Use realistic test data and fixtures
- Test both positive and negative scenarios
- Verify edge cases and error conditions

### Code Coverage
- Aim for >80% code coverage
- Focus on critical business logic
- Use coverage reports to identify gaps
- Avoid testing generated code
- Implement coverage thresholds in CI/CD

### Test Automation
- Integrate tests into CI/CD pipeline
- Run tests on every commit
- Implement parallel test execution
- Use test result reporting and notifications
- Implement test retry mechanisms for flaky tests

### Mocking & Stubbing
- Use mocks for external dependencies
- Implement realistic stub data
- Avoid over-mocking (test integration points)
- Use factories for complex test data
- Implement proper cleanup after tests

### Test Data Management
- Use fixtures for consistent test data
- Implement test data factories
- Separate test data from production data
- Use database transactions for test isolation
- Implement proper test data cleanup

### Performance Testing
- Define performance benchmarks
- Test under various load conditions
- Monitor resource usage
- Identify performance bottlenecks
- Implement performance regression tests

### Accessibility Testing
- Test with screen readers
- Verify keyboard navigation
- Check color contrast ratios
- Test responsive design
- Implement automated accessibility checks